1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 15.8, as
3 last amended by Section 2, Chapter 192, O.S.L. 2025 (59 O.S. Supp.
4 2025, Section 15.8), is amended to read as follows:
5 Section 15.8. A. A qualification applicant to qualify as a
6 candidate for examination shall file an application for
7 qualification in a format approved by the Oklahoma Accountancy
8 Board. The fee for the qualification application shall be
9 determined by the Board and shall not exceed Three Hundred Dollars
10 ($300.00). Every qualification applicant to qualify as a candidate
11 for the certificate of certified public accountant shall meet the
12 education and experience requirements, except as otherwise provided
13 in this section, at the time of filing the application for
14 qualification, shall meet the education requirements as provided in
15 this section.
16 B. On or after November 1, 2025, every qualification applicant
17 to qualify as a candidate for examination for the certificate of
18 certified public accountant shall have at least one hundred twenty
19 (120) semester hours, or the equivalent thereof, of college
20 education including a baccalaureate or higher degree, or the
21 equivalent thereof, conferred by a college or university acceptable
22 to the Board from an accredited four-year college or university in
23 this state or any other accredited four-year college or university
24 recognized by the Board. The total educational program of the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4317 SFLR Page 2
