4 equivalent thereof, in accounting courses above principles of
5 accounting or introductory accounting, with at least one course in
6 auditing or assurance; the remaining accounting courses shall be
7 selected from financial accounting, accounting theory,
8 cost/managerial accounting, federal income tax, governmental, not-
9 for-profit accounting, accounting information systems, accounting
10 history and other accounting electives; at least nine (9) semester
11 hours shall be from any or all of the subjects of economics,
12 statistics, business law, finance, business management, marketing,
13 business communication, risk management, insurance, management
14 information systems, or computer science at the upper-division level
15 of college or above or the equivalent of such subjects as determined
16 by the Board; all the remaining semester hours, if any, shall be
17 elective.
18 C. The costs associated with the national criminal history
19 record check shall be paid by the applicant.
