12 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 15.9, as
13 last amended by Section 2, Chapter 192, O.S.L. 2025 (59 O.S. Supp.
14 2025, Section 15.9), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 15.9. A. Upon payment of appropriate fees, the
16 Oklahoma Accountancy Board shall grant a certificate to any
17 individual of good character who meets the applicable education,
18 experience and testing requirements provided for in this section and
19 in Sections 15.8 and 15.10 of this title. For purposes of this
20 subsection, good character means an individual who does not have a
21 history of dishonest acts as demonstrated by documented evidence and
22 has not been convicted, pled guilty, or pled nolo contendere to a
23 felony charge. The Board may refuse to grant a certificate to an
24 applicant for failure to satisfy the requirement of good character.
