4 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 15.13, as
5 last amended by Section 6, Chapter 26, O.S.L. 2025 (59 O.S. Supp.
6 2025, Section 15.13), is amended to read as follows:
7 Section 15.13. A. The Oklahoma Accountancy Board may issue a
8 certificate to an applicant who has been authorized to practice
9 public accounting as a certified public accountant pursuant to the
10 laws of any jurisdiction if the applicant passed a test administered
11 for the purpose of authorizing an individual to practice as a
12 certified public accountant with grades which were equivalent to
13 passing a test for the same purpose in this state as of the date the
14 applicant originally passed the examination, and the applicant:
15 1. Meets the requirements for issuance of a certificate in this
16 state on the date of making application;
17 2. Met, on the date the certificate was issued by the other
18 jurisdiction, the requirements in effect on that date for issuance
19 of a certificate in this state; or
20 3. Met, on the date of becoming a candidate in another
21 jurisdiction, the requirements of becoming a candidate in this
22 state, except for residency
23 submits proof as provided by Board rule of completion of the
24 licensure requirements of his or her original licensing jurisdiction
